SIMPLE: clothe
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Clothe
<hw>Clothe</hw> <pr>(kl⟦omac⟧⟦th⟧)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Clothed</conjf>
<pr>(kl⟦omac⟧⟦th⟧d)</pr> <it>or</it> <conjf>Clad</conjf>
<pr>(kl⟦acr⟧d)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Clothing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>clathen</ets>,
<ets>clothen</ets>, <ets>clethen</ets>, AS. <ets>cl⟦amac⟧⟦edh⟧ian</ets>,
<ets>cl⟦aemac⟧⟦edh⟧an</ets>. See <er>Cloth</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To put garments on; to cover with clothing; to dress.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Go with me, to <qex>clothe</qex> you as becomes you.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To provide with clothes; <as>as, to feed and
<ex>clothe</ex> a family; to <ex>clothe</ex> one's self
extravagantly</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Drowsiness shall <qex>clothe</qex> a man with rags.</q>
<rj><qau>Prov. xxiii. 21.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The naked every day he <qex>clad</qex>,⟦br⟧
When he put on his clothes.</q> <rj><qau>Goldsmith.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Fig.: To cover or invest, as with a garment; <as>as,
to <ex>clothe</ex> one with authority or power</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Language in which they can <qex>clothe</qex> their thoughts.</q>
<rj><qau>Watts.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His sides are <qex>clothed</qex> with waving wood.</q> <rj><qau>J.
Dyer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thus Belial, with with words <qex>clothed</qex> in reason's
garb.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Clothe</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Clothe
<hw>Clothe</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To wear
clothes.</def> <mark>[Poetic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Care no more to <qex>clothe</qex> eat.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>clothed</ent>⟦br⟧
